VALUES
(40, 10, 40, 42, 10, 16, 16, 'he that receiveth you receiveth me', 'Reception and Rejection of Messengers', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between receiving or hearing the messengers and their connection to Jesus and God. They highlight that accepting or rejecting the messengers directly correlates to accepting or rejecting Jesus and the one who sent him.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 40, 40, 18, 5, 5, 'receiveth me', 'Receiving Christ and His Followers', 'Both passages emphasize the act of receiving as a means of receiving Christ. The first verse connects receiving Jesus'' followers to receiving Him, while the second highlights receiving a child in His name as receiving Him.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 40, 40, 25, 40, 40, 'he that receiveth me', 'Connection of Reception and Action', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between receiving and serving. In Matthew 10:40, receiving the disciples equates to receiving Jesus, while in Matthew 25:40, serving the least is equated with serving Jesus.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 40, 41, 9, 37, 37, 'he that receiveth me receiveth him that sent me', 'Reception of Jesus and the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of receiving. They highlight that receiving Jesus or his representatives equates to receiving God, establishing a direct link between the two verses.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 40, 43, 20, 21, 21, 'he that receiveth you receiveth me', 'Sending and Reception of Messengers', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being sent and received. In Matthew, receiving the messenger equates to receiving Jesus, while in John, Jesus sends his disciples as he was sent by the Father.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 41, 64, 1, 5, 8, 'receiveth a righteous man', 'Receiving Righteous Individuals', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving and supporting those who serve God. Matthew highlights the rewards for receiving prophets and righteous individuals, while 3 John encourages hospitality towards brethren and those on a godly journey.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 41, 58, 6, 10, 10, 'receive a prophet's reward', 'Reward for Service to Others', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving and ministering to others, highlighting that acts of service towards prophets and saints are recognized by God. This connection illustrates the theme of divine reward for those who support and serve God''s messengers and people.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 41, 12, 4, 8, 10, 'receiveth a prophet in the name of a prophet', 'Hospitality to God''s Messengers', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving a prophet or a righteous man. The Shunammite woman''s hospitality towards Elisha reflects the principle in Matthew about receiving a prophet in the name of a prophet.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 41, 12, 4, 16, 17, 'receiveth a prophet in the name of a prophet', 'Reward for Receiving Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of receiving a prophet. In Matthew, the reward for receiving a prophet is highlighted, while in 2 Kings, the woman who receives Elisha, a man of God, is blessed with a son as a reward.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 41, 42, 14, 13, 14, 'receive a prophet's reward', 'Reward for Welcoming the Needy', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving those in need and promise a reward for such actions. Matthew highlights the reward for receiving prophets and righteous individuals, while Luke speaks of blessings for inviting the poor and marginalized to a feast.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 41, 11, 18, 3, 4, 'receiveth a prophet in the name of a prophet', 'Reward for Receiving Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving prophets and righteous individuals. In Matthew, the reward for receiving a prophet is highlighted, while in 1 Kings, Obadiah''s actions in hiding and feeding the prophets demonstrate his recognition and support for them.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 41, 63, 1, 8, 8, 'receive a prophet's reward', 'Reward for Receiving Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of receiving a reward based on one''s actions towards prophets and righteous individuals. Matthew highlights the importance of receiving a prophet or righteous man, while 2 John warns to ensure we receive a full reward for our efforts.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 42, 58, 6, 10, 10, 'in the name of a disciple', 'Reward for Acts of Service', 'This connection highlights the theme of God recognizing acts of service and love towards others. Both passages emphasize that even small acts, like giving a cup of water, are acknowledged and rewarded by God.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 42, 40, 25, 40, 40, 'one of these little ones', 'Service to the Least', 'This connection highlights the importance of serving those considered ''little'' or ''least.'' Both passages emphasize that acts of kindness, even small ones like giving a cup of water, are significant and rewarded.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 42, 41, 9, 41, 42, 'a cup of cold water', 'Connection of Rewards for Service', 'Both passages emphasize the reward for giving a cup of water in Jesus'' name. They also highlight the significance of caring for ''little ones'' who believe in Him.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 42, 40, 18, 10, 10, 'these little ones', 'Connection of Care for Little Ones', 'This connection highlights the importance of caring for ''these little ones'' in both passages. Matthew 10:42 emphasizes the reward for acts of kindness towards them, while Matthew 18:10 warns against despising them, indicating their significance in the eyes of God.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 42, 47, 9, 6, 15, 'a cup of cold water', 'Connection of Generosity and Reward', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of giving generously and the rewards associated with such actions. Matthew highlights the act of giving even a small amount, while 2 Corinthians elaborates on the principle that generous giving leads to abundant blessings.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 42, 50, 4, 15, 19, 'in the name of a disciple', 'Connection of Generosity and Reward', 'This connection highlights the theme of generosity and its rewards. Both passages emphasize the importance of giving to others, with Matthew noting that even a small act, like giving a cup of cold water, will not go unrewarded, while Philippians speaks of the fruit that abounds from the Philippians'' support of Paul.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 10, 42, 41, 12, 42, 43, 'in the name of a disciple', 'Value of Small Acts', 'This connection highlights the significance of seemingly small acts of generosity. Both passages emphasize that even minimal contributions, like a cup of water or two mites, are valued greatly in the eyes of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 1, 23, 61, 1, 3, 'to teach and to preach', 'Connection of Preaching and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the act of preaching to those in need. Matthew 11:1 mentions Jesus teaching and preaching, while Isaiah 61:1 speaks of bringing good tidings and binding up the brokenhearted.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 1, 40, 9, 35, 35, NULL, 'Jesus'' Teaching and Preaching Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' role in teaching and preaching in cities. Matthew 11:1 follows the commissioning of the disciples, echoing the earlier description in Matthew 9:35 of Jesus'' own ministry in the cities and villages.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 1, 42, 4, 15, 21, 'to teach and to preach', 'Teaching and Preaching Ministry', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' role in teaching and preaching, as seen in both passages. In Matthew, Jesus commands his disciples to teach and preach, while in Luke, he actively engages in teaching in the synagogue.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 1, 42, 8, 1, 1, 'preach in their cities', 'Jesus'' Ministry in Cities', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' activity in cities and villages, highlighting his role in preaching. The mention of the twelve disciples accompanying him in both verses reinforces their involvement in this ministry.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 1, 44, 10, 38, 38, NULL, 'Jesus'' Ministry and Actions', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' active ministry as he ''went about doing good'' and ''teaching and preaching'' in various cities. Both passages emphasize the presence of divine empowerment in his actions, indicating that God was with him during his ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 1, 52, 4, 2, 2, 'commanding his twelve disciples', 'Commandments of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the transmission of Jesus'' teachings. Both passages emphasize the commandments given by Jesus to his followers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 1, 53, 3, 6, 6, 'commanding his twelve disciples', 'Commanding Discipleship and Conduct', 'This connection highlights the theme of command in both passages. Jesus commands his disciples to teach, while Paul commands the Thessalonians to withdraw from disorderly conduct.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 2, 41, 6, 17, 17, 'John had heard in the prison', 'Connection of John the Baptist''s Imprisonment', 'This connection highlights John''s imprisonment in both passages. Matthew mentions John in prison while Mark explains the reason for his imprisonment.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 2, 40, 14, 3, 3, 'in the prison', 'Connection Between John and Herod', 'Both passages emphasize John being in prison. The imprisonment of John in Matthew 14:3 sets the context for his inquiry about Christ''s works in Matthew 11:2.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 2, 40, 4, 12, 12, NULL, 'John''s Imprisonment and Jesus'' Ministry', 'This connection highlights the sequence of events surrounding John the Baptist''s imprisonment and Jesus'' subsequent ministry. Both passages emphasize John''s imprisonment as a pivotal moment that influences Jesus'' actions.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 11, 2, 42, 7, 18, 35, NULL, 'John''s Inquiry about Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize John the Baptist''s inquiry about Jesus'' identity, as he sends his disciples to ask, ''Art thou he that should come?'' This connection highlights John''s role in recognizing Jesus as the Messiah and seeking confirmation of his mission.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
